# Scanner and GS1 Safety

- Never break preservation of GS = `char 0x1D`.
- Do not replace GS with text, whitespace, Enter, Tab, or visible placeholder characters.
- Use escaped `[GS]` only for display/log UI, never as the stored or printed payload.
- Do not cut AI 92 by fixed length.
- Do not alter AI 91, AI 92, AI 93, or the crypto tail unless explicitly requested and tested.
- Do not rewrite RawInput, COM, scanner buffering, or GS1 parsing without focused tests.
- Do not use real Chestny ZNAK codes in tests, logs, documentation, prompts, or memory.
- Before touching scanner/parser code, read the RawInput, Serial, `Gs1Parser`, and `Gs1BarcodeEncoding` files.
